<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-035-203 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 440 433</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Oct 14 1991 v13 n41 p42(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>LapLink Pro offers 'smart' PC file transfers. (Traveling Softwareintroduces LapLink Pro file-transfer software) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Johnston, Stuart J.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Traveling Software announces LapLink Pro, a new version of itspopular file-transfer software that offers 'smart' transfers onlaptop computers.andP;  LapLink Pro directly supports more than 60Hayes-compatible modems and works over serial and parallelconnections between microcomputers.andP;  It includes 8-footlightweight 'TravelLite' cables and a 'universal communicationsobject' code module that recognizes the hardware it is running onand the parameters of the computer's communications system.andP;  Userscan send LapLink Pro itself over an existing connection to aremote computer.andP;  A Synchronize command lets the user makeselected directories on two identical drives and copy filesbetween them until both directories contain the same files.andP;  Amacro-like batch function can automate repetitive tasks, and asample editor with a clipboard feature is included.andP;  LapLink Procomes with both 3.5-inch and 5.25-inch disks and runs on anyIBM-compatible microcomputer with 440Kbytes of free RAM and DOS2.11 or later.andP;  Pricing is $149.95 until Dec 31, 1991 and $169.95thereafter; registered users of current versions can upgrade for$39.95.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Traveling Software Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   LapLink Pro (Communications software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionFile TransferCommunications software.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>